<Author>Sussexbabe
<Content>Stay here to be close to lively Las Ramblas but not on it!! We stayed at this hotel for 4 nights for our honeymoon. It is beautifully decorated and a very calming environment. Our room was huge with lots of space and although it faced the street there was never much noise at all. In fact the room was wonderful to come into after a hard day's walking as it had air-con. A real bonus was the electronic safe in the room which you programme with your own code when you arrive - that meant that we could leave everything (passports, extra cash, cards) in our room with no worries at all. The hotel is really well placed. It is 5 minutes walk to the bottom end of Las Ramblas (where there is also a metro station) or you can walk up through the old streets parallel to Las Ramblas to get to Placa de Catalunya - about a 20/25 minute walk from the hotel if you don't get distracted by other stuff! Cross the road in front of the hotel and walk over to Barceloneta  the beach - about 10-15 minutes walk with plenty of cafes on the way. We booked room only and didn't use the hotel for any food. The cost of food in the hotel struck us as expensive and so we used the cafes in the local area for breakfast - if you turn right when you come out of the hotel and walk towards Las Ramblas there is a little square a few minutes walk away. We breakfasted at tables in the square (2 coffees and croissants for 3 euros!) which was lovely in the summer sunshine. We also had breakfast twice at a cafe (La Gondeleria i think) which was down the street which runs at the back of the little square, walking towards Las Ramblas still - that was also good value and friendly. And also at the back of the little square is a restaurant called Fresco which is one of about 5 across Barcelona. There is a set charge for lunch or dinner (7 or 9 euros which includes a glass of wine!) and then you eat as much as you like from the delicious selection of salads, pasta and pizza. Overall, the hotel gave us a good base from which to explore Barcelona as it is well placed for the old town, Las Ramblas and the beach. 
